		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Principality of Monaco is a sovereign micro-state on the French Riviera. A Micro-state is a sovereign state with a small land and/or small population. Monaco is a country with less than 40,000 people, and less than 1 square mile of land(!). It is the second smallest micro-state in Europe after Vatican City. In the 12th century, a branch of the Genoa family, the Grimaldi, gained control of Monaco. The Grimaldi Family owned and ran Monaco for 500 years, though it changed hands briefly to Spain in the 13th century, and to the French Revolutionary forces in 1793. In 1861, Monaco was sold to France for 4 million francs, and the Franco-Monegasque Treaty recognized Monaco as a sovereign independent state. The 1910 Monegasque Revolution established that the
   
Grimaldi Family descendants have power to be absolute rulers of Monaco. Today, Monaco is run as a constitutional monarchy with the Prince of Monaco as the head of state overseeing the Executive Branch.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The economy of Monaco has flourished since the opening of the country’s first casino in the late 19th century: Monte Carlo. The direct railroads to France, it's beautiful scenery, and it's warm climate make Monaco a very attractive tourist destination. Monaco also has a major banking industry holding over 100 billion euro of funds. Since Monaco has no income taxes, and very low business taxes, it has provided a strong attraction for wealthy people. Thirty percent of the country’s population is made up of millionaires.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
